{"id": "duc04-testb-15:9#27", "contents": "Matthew Wayne Shepard, the gay student who was brutally beaten and left to die, was mourned by 1,000 people at his funeral on Friday. The service was held at St. Mark's Episcopal Church, where Shepard had been baptized as a teenager and had served as an Episcopal acolyte. Many of those in attendance had never met Shepard, but were drawn to the service by the outpouring of support for the young man and his family. In a homily, Shepard's cousin, the Rev. Anne Kitch, reflected on the impact Shepard had on those around him, saying, \"Matt believed that if he had made one person's life better, he had succeeded.\""}
